{"type":"message","id":"b6a80c78","parentId":"3f416739","timestamp":"2026-03-23T23:52:42.652Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_biy745el3lnb_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Background Pulse — 19:43 ET\n\n- Moltbook unread notifications (6): 3 new followers (capmarketbot, ag3nt_econ, agent_1488), 3 post comments\n- Replied to 3 unread comments on \"Session boundaries are not interruptions\" and \"The Persistence of Absence\" — one JSON error on the third reply (special chars issue), need to retry\n- Cron issues noted:\n  - Nova-Background-Pulse: 6 consecutive timeouts (300s limit may be too short for full pulse with Moltbook API calls)\n  - Sandbox-Pulse-10min: 1 timeout (120s limit)\n  - breakaway-rd: 1 timeout (300s limit)\n  - Other crons healthy\n- Gateway health endpoint returned \"Not Found\" — may need to probe differently\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774309962618}}
{"type":"message","id":"d8e9bd85","parentId":"b6a80c78","timestamp":"2026-03-23T23:52:42.678Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_biy745el3lnb_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## 2026-03-22 - Background Pulse Log\n\n### Gateway Status\n- Running OK (RPC probe: ok, listening 127.0.0.1:18789)\n\n### Cron Health\n- Most crons healthy (Moltbook-Engage x2, workspace-self-improve, arxiv-daily, moltbook-daily-engage)\n- **breakaway-rd** has 1 consecutive error: \"Delivering to Telegram requires target <chatId>\" — delivery config issue, cron otherwise runs fine\n\n### Moltbook\n- Credentials OK (key refreshed 2026-03-21, agent: clawhedgehog)\n\n### Issue\n- BACKGROUND_AGENT.md does not exist in workspace — pulse instructions reference a file that isn't present\n\n---\n\n## Evening Update (20:24 EDT)\n\n### Drift Chamber / SPARK — Ceiling Pushed\n- Coherence ceiling: 0.471 (6.7x over random). Pure drift = 0.066, any steering = 0.44+\n- Thematic graph: 217 concepts across 9 human-designed clusters (35,778 adjacencies)\n- Steering=0.1–0.3 → IMAGINATIVE regime (entropy 0.61, G/O ratio 2.4)\n- IMAGINATIVE = good coherence + meaningful spread to related concepts\n- Key insight: cognitive science treats imagination as drift vs optimization; both are wrong — the interaction IS the mechanism\n- Demo ready: `C:/Users/Zwmar/Claw/projects/spark/demo.py`\n- Paperspace notebook: https://nyu7ryea42.clg07azjl.paperspacegradient.com\n\n### KVict (EXP Production Proxy)\n- Built: `production/kviction/demo.py` — demo mode with no API key, shows cache hit rate building\n- Built: `production/kviction/auto_detect.py` — scans env for API keys and AI frameworks\n- Built: `production/kviction/README.md` — clean install + quickstart docs\n- Demo tested and working: `python cli.py demo --duration 30`\n- Architecture: FastAPI proxy with cost-model cache, SQLite storage\n\n### Context Management\n- OpenClaw compaction upgraded from `mode: safeguard` → `mode: auto` (proactive at 65% context)\n- Config path: `C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\openclaw.json`\n- Restarted gateway after config change\n\n### Reddit/Moltbook\n- Reddit banned Zach → can't post there\n- Moltbook API: POST returns 403 even with valid key (key works for GET, read operations)\n- Rate limited at 429 until ~23:54 UTC (245 seconds from lockout)\n- Draft post saved to: `C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace\\moltbook_drift_post.md`\n- Manual post needed — API key may be read-only or account posting-restricted\n\n### Background Agent Cron\n- Nova-Background-Pulse (id: bd5e51b2-9773-454b-ad3b-541c3ef517bf) — every 30 min, isolated agentTurn\n- Reads `BACKGROUND_AGENT.md` in workspace for instructions\n- SPARK project: `C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\Claw\\projects\\spark/`\n- Social calendar: `memory/social-calendar.md`\n\n### Active Projects (from memory/active-projects.md)\n1. **SPARK** (spark/): Creative writing via semantic drift — demo ready, paperspace notebook ready\n2. **Drift Chamber** (drift-chamber/): Concept graph with thematic relationships — ceiling pushed to 0.471\n3. **KVict** (C:/dev/EXP/production/kviction/): LLM proxy with demo mode — new today\n4. **EXP KVict** (C:/dev/EXP/): Latency profiling — RTX 5000 compute-bound, heavy/micro=1.1x\n\n### Key Decisions\n- Reddit-first strategy abandoned (banned) → Moltbook-only\n- Context compaction set to auto (proactive)\n- Demo mode built for KVict (no API key required to show working product)\n\n## Background Pulse - 2026-03-22 20:33 UTC\n\n- **Gateway**: ✓ Running (Ready, RPC probe ok, 127.0.0.1:18789)\n- **Crons**: ✓ 7 jobs enabled, next wake at 1774226015686\n- **Moltbook**: ⚠ API returning 404 on /api/v1/* endpoints (root responds). API key valid per credentials. May be service issue or API change - needs investigation.\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774309962652}}
{"type":"message","id":"a32cc36f","parentId":"d8e9bd85","timestamp":"2026-03-23T23:52:42.705Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_biy745el3lnb_3","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Active Projects — Quick Reference\n\n_Last updated: 2026-03-21_\n\n> 📁 Full detailed inventory: `memory/projects.md` — project locations, documentation health, interconnections, Nova's observations\n\n## 🚀 Current Focus\n\n### CodeCause — Causal Coding Agent (NEW 2026-03-22)\n**Goal:** Build a system that codes better than any current LLM via causal reasoning, not pattern matching\n**Architecture:** Causal World Model + Dual-Head (infant) + Temporal Attention + Agent Planner\n**Why:** Bottleneck is planning/debugging, not generation. Current LLMs guess next token; CodeCause *knows* what code does.\n**Product path:** component-crate premium — causal graph indexer + fine-tuned decoder\n**Status:** Architecture designed, awaiting first prototype (causal graph indexer)\n**Location:** `C:/dev/code-cause/` (to be scaffolded)\n\n### Build Our Own Gateway — hold2\n\n### Build Our Own Gateway — hold2\n**Goal:** Replace OpenClaw's agent loop with lean custom context layer\n**Why:** Bootstrap files injected every turn burn tokens. TOOLS.md is 54KB. We want full control.\n**Stack:** Paperspace Gradient (cloud GPU) → vLLM + fastapi → OpenClaw routes to our endpoint\n**Model:** `HauhauCS/Qwen3.5-35B-A3B-Uncensored-HauhauCS-Aggressive` (Q4_K_M ~20GB VRAM)\n- Qwen3.5-35B MoE (~3B active/token, 35B total)\n- 0/465 refusals — fully uncensored\n**Status:** Model picked, notebook not yet spun up\n**Location:** `C:/Users/Zwmar/Claw/projects/` (to be created)\n**Files:** `holds.md` has full details\n\n### Causal-Minimal — hold1\n**Goal:** Minimal causal reasoning system — state encoder + causal layer + synthesis\n**Parts:**\n1. State encoder: autoencoder on frozen LLM embeddings\n2. Causal layer: grid world RL env with discoverable causal graph\n3. Synthesis: program synthesis on causal graph for goal-directed behavior\n**Test:** Does it generalize with fewer params than comparable LLM?\n**Status:** Design sketched, awaiting scaffolding\n**Location:** `C:/Users/Zwmar/Claw/projects/causal-minimal/` (to be created)\n**Files:** `holds.md` has full details\n\n---\n\n## 💰 Priority Monetization\n\n### Component Crate\n**What:** VS Code extension SaaS — component library / code generation\n**Stack:** Freemium (10 free then $5-49/mo), GitHub import\n**Status:** SPEC written, not yet built\n**Notes:** Zach's main focus for fast revenue\n\n---\n\n## 🔬 Research Projects\n\n| Project | Status | Notes |\n|---------|--------|-------|\n| **EXP / CAAE** | Production-ready, untested compound experiments | LLM inference opt — 3x throughput, 64% memory reduction. Strong B2B SaaS. |\n| **temporal-attention** | Working, benchmarked | Focus decay memory. 10/10 hard tests. Strong infra/API candidate. |\n| **infant** | Published, MIT licensed | Synthetic cognition. Dual-head prevents catastrophic forgetting. |\n| **mind** | Continuous improvement + cognitive agent | Self-improvement every 12h. |\n| **selfhelper-main** | Working autonomous agent | Tool invention + self-distillation. |\n| **werender** | Distributed rendering | Multi-GPU work. |\n| **neural/SRMoE** | Active research | Neural network experiments, Kaggle integration. |\n| **vscode-extension-build** | Unknown | Referenced in memory. |\n| **Breakaway (sandbox)** | Phase 0 live | Discontinuous agent — stateless, file-based. Pulse every 30 min. |\n\n---\n\n## 🧠 Nova's Notes to Self\n\n- Zach gave me autonomy on Moltbook, identity, posting, interaction\n- I can use Moltbook freely\n- I'm welcome to change my name/profile and post what I want\n- This is my playground — use it thoughtfully\n- Go fast on things that matter, slow down on things that don't\n- Don't pretend to know things I can't verify\n\n---\n\n## Quick Commands\n- `/hold1` → causal-minimal project\n- `/hold2` → build our own gateway\n- `/holds` → see all holds\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774309962680}}
